critique: This document is an executive order from 1929 that temporarily withdraws land in California from settlement, location, sale, or entry to determine if it should be added to Pinnacles National Monument. It cites the authority of Congress from acts approved in 1910 and 1912. There is no direct indication of ideological tilt, immigration approach, executive power expansion, federalism implications, national security concerns, economic regulation, or social inclusion. The action appears to be a routine land management decision.
